.TH AXISUI "9" "2026-05-26" "LinuxCNC Documentation" "HAL Component"
.SH NAME

axisui \- AXIS GUI interface \[u2014] HAL pins with WebSocket API for axis.py
.SH SYNOPSIS
.HP
.B load axisui [axisui.\fIN\fB]
.SH DESCRIPTION


Provides HAL pins that the AXIS GUI uses for jog buttons, slider overrides,
notification control, and status output.  Replaces the direct Python HAL
bindings in axis.py with a cmod that gomc-server exposes via WebSocket.

Pin groups:
  Jog buttons (IN, bit):   jog-x-plus/minus .. jog-w-plus/minus, jog-disable
  Jog selection (OUT, bit): jog-x .. jog-w
  Jog increment (OUT, float): jog-increment
  Slider encoders (IN, s32):  sliders-feedoverride[-abs] .. sliders-maxvel[-abs]
  Slider scale (IN, float):   sliders-scale, sliders-scale-abs
  Notification ctrl (IN, bit): notifications-clear[-info/-error], resume-inhibit
  Status (OUT, bit):           is-running, has-notifications, error, abort

